57/* X509 v3 extension utilities */
58
59#include <stdio.h>
60
61#include <openssl/bio.h>
62#include <openssl/conf.h>
63#include <openssl/mem.h>
64#include <openssl/x509v3.h>
65
66
67/* Extension printing routines */
68
69static int unknown_ext_print(BIO *out, X509_EXTENSION *ext, unsigned long flag, int indent, int supported);
70
71/* Print out a name+value stack */
72
73void X509V3_EXT_val_prn(BIO *out, STACK_OF(CONF_VALUE) *val, int indent, int ml)
74{
75 size_t i;
76 CONF_VALUE *nval;
77 if(!val) return;
78 if(!ml || !sk_CONF_VALUE_num(val)) {
79 BIO_printf(out, "%*s", indent, "");
80 if(!sk_CONF_VALUE_num(val)) BIO_puts(out, "<EMPTY>\n");
81 }
82 for(i = 0; i < sk_CONF_VALUE_num(val); i++) {
83 if(ml) BIO_printf(out, "%*s", indent, "");
84 else if(i > 0) BIO_printf(out, ", ");
85 nval = sk_CONF_VALUE_value(val, i);
86 if(!nval->name) BIO_puts(out, nval->value);
87 else if(!nval->value) BIO_puts(out, nval->name);
88 else BIO_printf(out, "%s:%s", nval->name, nval->value);
89 if(ml) BIO_puts(out, "\n");
90 }
91}
92
93/* Main routine: print out a general extension */
94
95int X509V3_EXT_print(BIO *out, X509_EXTENSION *ext, unsigned long flag, int indent)
96{
97 void *ext_str = NULL;
98 char *value = NULL;
99 const unsigned char *p;
100 const X509V3_EXT_METHOD *method;
101 STACK_OF(CONF_VALUE) *nval = NULL;
102 int ok = 1;
103
104 if(!(method = X509V3_EXT_get(ext)))
105 return unknown_ext_print(out, ext, flag, indent, 0);
106 p = ext->value->data;
107 if(method->it) ext_str = ASN1_item_d2i(NULL, &p, ext->value->length, ASN1_ITEM_ptr(method->it));
108 else ext_str = method->d2i(NULL, &p, ext->value->length);
109
110 if(!ext_str) return unknown_ext_print(out, ext, flag, indent, 1);
111
112 if(method->i2s) {
113 if(!(value = method->i2s(method, ext_str))) {
114 ok = 0;
115 goto err;
116 }
117 BIO_printf(out, "%*s%s", indent, "", value);
118 } else if(method->i2v) {
119 if(!(nval = method->i2v(method, ext_str, NULL))) {
120 ok = 0;
121 goto err;
122 }
123 X509V3_EXT_val_prn(out, nval, indent,
124 method->ext_flags & X509V3_EXT_MULTILINE);
125 } else if(method->i2r) {
126 if(!method->i2r(method, ext_str, out, indent)) ok = 0;
127 } else ok = 0;
128
129 err:
130 sk_CONF_VALUE_pop_free(nval, X509V3_conf_free);
131 if(value) OPENSSL_free(value);
132 if(method->it) ASN1_item_free(ext_str, ASN1_ITEM_ptr(method->it));
133 else method->ext_free(ext_str);
134 return ok;
135}
136
137int X509V3_extensions_print(BIO *bp, const char *title, STACK_OF(X509_EXTENSION) *exts, unsigned long flag, int indent)
138{
139 size_t i;
140 int j;
141
142 if(sk_X509_EXTENSION_num(exts) <= 0) return 1;
143
144 if(title)
145 {
146 BIO_printf(bp,"%*s%s:\n",indent, "", title);
147 indent += 4;
148 }
149
150 for (i=0; i<sk_X509_EXTENSION_num(exts); i++)
151 {
152 ASN1_OBJECT *obj;
153 X509_EXTENSION *ex;
154 ex=sk_X509_EXTENSION_value(exts, i);
155 if (indent && BIO_printf(bp,"%*s",indent, "") <= 0) return 0;
156 obj=X509_EXTENSION_get_object(ex);
157 i2a_ASN1_OBJECT(bp,obj);
158 j=X509_EXTENSION_get_critical(ex);
159 if (BIO_printf(bp,": %s\n",j?"critical":"") <= 0)
160 return 0;
161 if(!X509V3_EXT_print(bp, ex, flag, indent + 4))
162 {
163 BIO_printf(bp, "%*s", indent + 4, "");
164 M_ASN1_OCTET_STRING_print(bp,ex->value);
165 }
166 if (BIO_write(bp,"\n",1) <= 0) return 0;
167 }
168 return 1;
169}
170
171static int unknown_ext_print(BIO *out, X509_EXTENSION *ext, unsigned long flag, int indent, int supported)
172{
173 switch(flag & X509V3_EXT_UNKNOWN_MASK) {
174
175 case X509V3_EXT_DEFAULT:
176 return 0;
177
178 case X509V3_EXT_ERROR_UNKNOWN:
179 if(supported)
180 BIO_printf(out, "%*s<Parse Error>", indent, "");
181 else
182 BIO_printf(out, "%*s<Not Supported>", indent, "");
183 return 1;
184
185 case X509V3_EXT_PARSE_UNKNOWN:
186 return ASN1_parse_dump(out,
187 ext->value->data, ext->value->length, indent, -1);
188 case X509V3_EXT_DUMP_UNKNOWN:
189 return BIO_hexdump(out, ext->value->data, ext->value->length, indent);
190
191 default:
192 return 1;
193 }
194}
195
196
197#ifndef OPENSSL_NO_FP_API
198int X509V3_EXT_print_fp(FILE *fp, X509_EXTENSION *ext, int flag, int indent)
199{
200 BIO *bio_tmp;
201 int ret;
202 if(!(bio_tmp = BIO_new_fp(fp, BIO_NOCLOSE))) return 0;
203 ret = X509V3_EXT_print(bio_tmp, ext, flag, indent);
204 BIO_free(bio_tmp);
205 return ret;
206}
207#endif
